  "prompt": "What are some good young hard rock artist similar to bands like Rage Against The Machine, Wakrat, Foo Fighters, Downset, ACDC and Xombie etc?",
  "response": "There are several young and upcoming hard rock artists that embody the energy and intensity similar to bands like Rage Against The Machine, Wakrat, Foo Fighters, Downset, AC/DC, and Xombie. Here are a few recommendations:\n\n1. **Royal Blood**: This British duo delivers hard-hitting rock with powerful bass riffs and dynamic drumming. Their music has a raw intensity that echoes classic rock and hard rock bands.\n\n2. **Goodbye June**: This American rock band combines southern rock influences with hard rock energy. Their powerful vocals and electrifying guitar work make them reminiscent of bands like AC/DC.\n\n3. **Cleopatrick**: Canadian rock duo Cleopatrick is known for their heavy riffs and raw, gritty sound. They bring a fresh perspective to hard rock that is both energetic and rebellious, similar to artists like Rage Against The Machine.\n\n4. **Black Pistol Fire**: This explosive American duo blends high-energy rock with blues influences. Their sound is intense and powerful, much like Foo Fighters and AC/DC.\n\n5. **Highly Suspect**: Massachusetts-based Highly Suspect brings a mix of hard rock and alternative influences. Their music is full of emotion and raw energy, making them a great fit for fans of Rage Against The Machine and Foo Fighters.\n\n6. **Greta Van Fleet**: Often compared to Led Zeppelin due to their classic rock influences, Greta Van Fleet brings a modern twist to hard rock with soaring vocals and masterful instrumentation.\n\n7. **The Blue Stones**: This Canadian duo delivers a blend of hard rock and blues with powerful guitar riffs and energetic rhythms. Their sound is reminiscent of bands like Foo Fighters and Royal Blood.\n\n8. **Starcrawler**: Los Angeles-based Starcrawler captures the wild spirit of hard rock with their raw energy and theatrical performances. Their music is gritty and intense, akin to the rebelliousness of Downset and Rage Against The Machine.\n\nThese artists are contributing to the evolution of hard rock while staying true to the genre's powerful roots.",
